	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f96749633022230>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=>Weapon Damage</a> <a id=fs8 href=#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Aug 28th 4:58 PM 2000</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>What is the real damage for my wepon?&nbsp;&nbsp;IE. if I have a X damage weapon what is the real damage I do?  Anyone know any good websites with damage info.<br><br>Thanks&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan=2 align=right class=mform id=fs8>2 Replies</td></tr>
	     </form></table><tr><td colspan=2><ul><table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f9693246506307>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=5&mid=9693246506307>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=5&mid=9693246506307>RE: Weapon Damage</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=5&mid=9693246506307#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Sep 18th 8:50 PM 2000</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=492><span id=Sage>Gorthin</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>161 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.67]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>*NOTE*&nbsp;&nbsp;Af of 09/19/00 they changed the formulae for 2h weapons (all) and also 1h weapons WITH A HIGH DELAY (40+).  2h Weapons with a delay of 29 or below had their damage bonus reduced, 30-39 were left alone, and all weapons with a delay of 40+ had the bonus increased according to Verant.  No specifics as of yet.<br><br><br>I am going to post what I have read from a couple other places, along with my experiences so far.<br><br>Maximum damage is calculated as ((Weapon dmg)*2) +1, BEFORE any other bonuses due to Str, Level, or the weapon bonus (see a little later) are added.  For example, if you are wielding a 9 Dmg weapon, you will do (9*2) +1 or 19 maximum.  As you get higher in level, your strength, combined with any level bonuses and just an naturally increasing Attack level will change this.<br><br>For Level 1-9, the "cap" is 19.<br>For level 10-19 the "cap" is 29.<br>For level 20-29 the "cap" is 59. *****This one is speculation, as I read a 30 dmg weapon has another cap to be dealt with until level 30******<br>For level 30+ There is no cap of which I am aware.<br><br>A high strength CAN push you past these caps.  For exaple, with my Troll from 1-9 hits of up to 22 were fairly common, and at 19 I occasioanlly saw a hit for 35 (With a 160 or so Str).  At 27 I can hit for 64 occasionally with a 21 dmg 2h Slash. (170 str).<br><br>Another thing to take into consideration is there is a weapon bonus determined by level.  This is a reminder:  I can NOT guarantee any of this information is 100% accurate.  This is from other posts from melee boards I have read!<br><br>The Two handed damage bonus is (Level -7)/3.  Hence if you are level 25, when you use a 2h weapon you will get (25-7)/3 or a 6 point bonus per hit to your MAXIMUM damage.  The reason I say Maximum is occasionally I still get a wimpy 2 point damage hit, although it is &gt;VERY&lt; rare.<br><br>The one handed bonus is (Level -25)/3.  Hence this does not kick in until 28+.<br><br>As your attack rating gets higher due to an increased weapon skill and offense, so will your maximum damage.  It seems with every level I have gotten, I have jumped 1 or 2 points in max damage for my 2h slash, and usually 1 point for my 1h slash.<br><br><br>With a 2h I hit for 21 over my straight maximum for weapon damage.  With 1h, I hit for up to 10 over.  This is at level 27 with a 168 str for 2h Slash and 178 or so for 1hslash.<br><br>Sorry I could not give any ironclad formulae, but these seems fairly accurate.  I am NOT claiming credit for these, they were posted on other boards and fall into line with Verant's statement that 2h weapons get a bigger damage bonus to offset the slower speeds.<br><br>Chugrak 27 Troll SK</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
